divs: sighting detailsi was sitting on the shore of the gulf of mexico watching the sun set. i took out my cell phone and took several shots of my surroundings and the sun. i really wasn't looking at what was in my camera frame at the time because i didn't have my glasses on. a few days later i downloaded the pictures to my computer and found that four consecutive frames had yellow spheres in them. the first one is in the water in front of me. the second is in the water to my left. the third is in the water to my right. the last is in the air going behind a cloud with a red field of light or energy around it. i took several other shots and a couple videos after those four shots and there aren't any yellow spheres in any of them. i have blown up these pictures x800 and they appear to have been behind the waves of the water. i personally can't figure out what they are\were and if there was one fast moving or several. willing to show my pictures and cell to anyone but not willing to email them.
